#: forms/templates/forms/rock_cannon_home.html:21
msgid "All about Rock Cannons"
msgstr "Popeth am Greigiau Cannan"

#: forms/templates/forms/rock_cannon_home.html:23
msgid ""
"A rock cannon is a method of salutation and the celebration of important "
"social, commercial and industrial events, whether they are of local or "
"national interest, that dates back as far as the latter years of the 18th "
"century. It was initially believed that this method of celebration was "
"confined to the slate quarries and metal mines of Gwynedd, but research has "
"now shown that sites exist in other parts of North Wales. As of 2001, 235 "
"sites have been found adding up to 6,157 holes."
msgstr "Mae canon craig yn ddull o gyfarch a dathlu digwyddiadau cymdeithasol, masnachol a diwydiannol pwysig, boed o ddiddordeb lleol neu genedlaethol, sy'n dyddio'n ôl cyn belled â blynyddoedd olaf y 18fed ganrif. Credwyd yn wreiddiol bod y dull hwn o ddathlu wedi'i gyfyngu i chwareli llechi a mwyngloddiau metel Gwynedd, ond mae ymchwil bellach wedi dangos bod safleoedd yn bodoli mewn rhannau eraill o Ogledd Cymru. Hyd at 2001, mae 235 o safleoedd wedi'u canfod yn cyfateb i 6,157 o dyllau."

#: forms/templates/forms/rock_cannon_home.html:26
msgid "Fun facts about Rock Cannons"
msgstr "Ffeithiau hwyl am Ganonau Creigiau"

#: forms/templates/forms/rock_cannon_home.html:28
msgid ""
"The earliest record of cannon in Gwynedd is found in a contemporary newspaper report (1808), which gives lengthy details of the celebration in various areas of present Gwynedd of the 50th anniversary of George III's accession to the throne. It states, under the heading of JUBILEE that 'In no part of the British Empire has this event been celebrated with greater demonstrations of rejoicing, thankfulness, and all the more estimable virtues of charity and beneficence, than in this principality'. Rock cannons were used to celebrate the marriage of Albert Edward, Prince of Wales to Princess Alexandra of Denmark in 1863 as well as the Diamond Jubilee of Queen Victoria in 1897."
msgstr "Mae'r cofnod cynharaf o ganon yng Ngwynedd i'w gael mewn adroddiad papur newydd cyfoes (1808), sy'n rhoi manylion hir am y dathliad mewn gwahanol ardaloedd o Wynedd bresennol o 50fed pen-blwydd esgyniad Siôr III i'r orsedd. Mae'n nodi, o dan y pennawd JIWBILI 'Nid yw'r digwyddiad hwn wedi'i ddathlu mewn unrhyw ran o Ymerodraeth Prydain gyda mwy o arddangosiadau o lawenydd, diolchgarwch, a holl rinweddau mwy gwerthfawr elusen a charedigrwydd, nag yn y dywysogaeth hon'. Defnyddiwyd canonau craig i ddathlu priodas Albert Edward, Tywysog Cymru â'r Dywysoges Alexandra o Ddenmarc ym 1863 yn ogystal â Jiwbilî Diemwnt y Frenhines Victoria ym 1897."

